    "body": "There should not be a difference but there are some caveats. I assume you are setting up a private network.\r\n\r\nFirst thing to check is that both nodes are connected. If not set up a boot node or add them manually with `admin.addPeer(enode)`.\r\n\r\nSecond, if only 1 of the nodes is mining and the transaction was sent from the other node there is a known issue that transaction are not accepted by the miner. Nodes start by default under the assumption they are not synchronized with the network. When not synchronized the node won't accept transactions since these transaction might already be included in the chain. After a node has imported a block from the network it assumes its synchronized and starts accepting transaction. Solution for now is to enable mining on both nodes.\r\n\r\n",
